Executive Profile
Glenn M. Renwick  Executive Chairman, The Progressive CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships62$9,793,407As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Glenn M. Renwick served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Progressive Corp. since January 2001 until July 1, 2016. Mr. Renwick served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Progressive Casualty Insurance Company since March 2000 to March 2004 and March 2003 respectively. His responsibilities are to establish and uphold Progressive's Vision, Core Values, financial objectives and strategies and to assist corporate leaders in strategic planning ... and communication. He served as the Chief Technology Officer of Progressive Casualty Insurance Company since March 2000. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Insurance Operations and Business Technology Process Leader at Progressive Corp. from 1998 to 2000 and also served as its Chief Information Officer from January 1998 to March 2000. He led Progressive's Consumer Marketing group and before he served as the President of various divisions within Progressive. He joined Progressive in 1986 as Auto Product Manager for Florida. Mr. Renwick has more than 25 years in the insurance industry. He has been Executive Chairman of Progressive Corp. since November 2013 and its Director since 1999. He served as Chairman of Progressive Casualty Insurance Company from March 2000 to March 2004. He has been the Chairman of Fiserv, Inc. since May 24, 2017. He serves as a Director of The Cleveland Play House. He has been an Independent Director at UnitedHealth Group Incorporated since June 2008. He served as a Director of Progressive Casualty Insurance Company. He has been an Independent Director of Fiserv, Inc. since November 2001. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board of PreEmptive Solutions, LLC. Mr. Renwick holds an Undergraduate Degree(Ms) in Mathematics and Economics from the University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand and a Master's Degree in Engineering from the University of Florida, Gainesville.Read Full Background




